message.content: The paper "Team Papelo Transformer Networks At Fever" likely belongs to the arXiv CS sub-categories of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language), "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence), "cs.LG" (Machine Learning), "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval), and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). This is because the paper discusses the development of a system for the FEVER fact extraction and verification challenge that uses transformer networks pretrained with language modeling, which is a common technique in these sub-fields of computer science. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing and machine learning, which are also common themes in these sub-categories.
